Two factory fires which broke out in the Pakistan cities of Karachi and Lahore have claimed 216 lives and injured dozens more.

Workers have revealed how they jumped from third floor windows to escape the blaze at a garment factory in Karachi, where many of the 191 victims were trapped in a basement.

In Lahore, staff at a shoe factory claimed a faulty generator sparked the fire which killed 25 people.

