Firefighters were still trying to subdue the blaze in Karachi this morning, as hospital staff revealed its morgue was full with 'around 30 bodies burnt beyond recognition all lined up'.

'People started screaming for their 
lives,' said factory worker Mohammad Asif, 20. 'Everyone came to the window. I jumped 
from the third floor.'

Another worker, Liaqat Hussain, 29, spoke from his hospital bed where he was being treated for burns all over his body. He said: 'Within two minutes there was fire in 
the entire factory.

'The gate was closed. There was no access to get out, we were trapped inside.'

Doomed: Firefighters remove the body of one of the trapped Karachi workers

